Write SQL Query 

Problem
Find Merchants with High Transaction Volume

Description
You are given a database table that stores transaction details for different merchants. Each record represents a single transaction made by a merchant.
Your task is to identify all merchants who have performed more than a specified number of transactions (e.g., more than 10 transactions).

Table Schema: MerchantTransactions

| Column Name       | Data Type | Description                           |
| ----------------- | --------- | ------------------------------------- |
| MerchantID        | INT       | Unique identifier for the merchant    |
| TransactionID     | INT       | Unique identifier for the transaction |
| TransactionAmount | DECIMAL   | Amount of the transaction             |
| TransactionDate   | DATE      | Date of the transaction               |

Sample Input

| MerchantID | TransactionID | TransactionAmount | TransactionDate |
| ---------- | ------------- | ----------------- | --------------- |
| 1          | 1             | 100               | 2024-04-08      |
| 1          | 2             | 50                | 2024-04-09      |
| 2          | 3             | 100               | 2024-04-15      |


Expected Output
Return a list of MerchantID values where the number of transactions is greater than 10.

SQL Solution

SELECT MerchantID, COUNT(TransactionID) AS txn_count
FROM MerchantTransactions
GROUP BY MerchantID
HAVING COUNT(TransactionID) > 10;
